title: Ali Zafar will not perform at PSL final ceremony
text:
GEO NEWS Posted on March 3, 2017 
LAHORE: Pakistani singer and actor Ali Zafar has announced that he will not be performing during the ceremony of the Pakistan Super League (PSL) final which will take place at the Gaddafi stadium on March 5. 
In a series of tweets, Ali Zafar said he was stuck with shooting schedule for a film. Contrary to the news, I won't be performing at the PSL closing ceremony. It is indeed a big moment, hope we get to celebrate in safety. — Ali Zafar (@AliZafarsays) March 3, 2017 1/2 I remember the moment while writing the lyrics "phir stage sajay ga" wishing our stadiums would once again experience the magic :) — Ali Zafar (@AliZafarsays) March 3, 2017 2/2 unfortunately stuck with shooting schedule for the film. But lots of love and prayers. #AbKhelJamayGa . #pakistanzindabad . — Ali Zafar (@AliZafarsays) March 3, 2017 More Stories From PSL
